<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,151,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species has male genitalia similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[909,1045,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata">
<emphasis box="[909,1045,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P. attenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[1103,1279,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoattenuata">
<emphasis box="[1103,1279,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P. neoattenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however the aedeagus in the new species lacks the flanges present in 
<taxonomicName box="[782,916,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata">
<emphasis box="[782,916,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P. attenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and dorsal keel in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[1128,1301,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoattenuata">
<emphasis box="[1128,1301,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P. neoattenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
